Fixed #92 by providing an API in ViewInfo to include the preferred component type for a view. This change results in the PREFERRED_VIEW policy category to be obsolete. Refactored existing component providers to use ViewInfo instead of policies to determine the preferred view. Another addition to the API of ViewInfo is to allow specification of whether this view should expand the full center pane (hiding both the list and inspector panes) when first opened into its own window. This is only used in the context where ViewInfo.viewType = ViewType.CENTER.

[MCT-3811] Fix for Canvas on canvas: Panel cannot be
selected, drag-drop throws exception.
Fixed the issue of selection of panel with a canvas. The issue was
that the selection was cleared by a call to panel.clearSelections. Moved
this call in front of the panel selection. 
Fixed the exception when performing a DnD of the canvas panel in the
canvas. An endless loop was initiated between panel and canvas for
selection changes when clearing selections. Now testing whether
any selection needs to be cleared, if not, no clearing is initiated
preventing the infinite loop.

selected, drag-drop throws exception.

any selection needs to be cleared, if not, no clearing is initiated
preventing the infinite loop.

[MCT-3782] Fix NPE for DnD operation from inspector title to canvas.
An NPE was raised due to setSelections clearing the transfer
handler in the inspector, causing the DnD framework not being able to
invoke exportDone. Now allowing DnD to complete and to perform the
selection of the dropped component(s) after DnD completes.

When user chooses a view type in inspector, this view type becomes the default view type for inspection. The initial default is the platform info view. If a component does not allow the platform info view to show up (e.g., policy controlled), then whichever the first viewinfo returned by AbstractComponent.getViewInfos() will show in the inspector. However, the view type of this view will not overwrite the default view type for inspection.

refactoring.

embedded multi
[MCT-3603] [multi] Misplaced error
[MCT-3589] Users can create objects via context menu even if a
composition policy exists and says they shouldn't be able to
The approach is to create a temporary component and check it against
target component using composition policy. If it fails, then don't add
the new object action for that component type.  Then the temp component
is deleted.  This prevents users, for example, from creating anything
inside a multi that doesn't have a feed view, fixing the reported multi
composition-related bugs.

Fixed MCT-3682 [Descendants] Reordering components causes duplicate
component references to appear in the same collection. Because the
list of child components is soft-referenced, a different list of
child components may be retrieved each time getComponents() is called.
So upon reordering/manipulting child components, we get a snapshot of
the child list and work on that list, instead of calling
getComponents() multiple times.
improve query performance when finding referenced components
